## CIDR Block

CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing) defines the IP address range of your VPC.

```
10.0.0.0/16  →  65,536 IP addresses  (10.0.0.0 to 10.0.255.255)
10.0.0.0/24  →  256 IP addresses     (10.0.0.0 to 10.0.0.255)
10.0.0.0/28  →  16 IP addresses      (smallest allowed in AWS)
```

AWS reserves **5 IPs** from every subnet:
```
10.0.1.0   → Network address
10.0.1.1   → VPC router
10.0.1.2   → DNS server
10.0.1.3   → Reserved for future use
10.0.1.255 → Broadcast address
```
So a /24 subnet gives you **251 usable IPs**, not 256.

