## NAT Gateway

NAT (Network Address Translation) Gateway allows instances in a **private subnet to initiate outbound internet connections** while **blocking inbound connections** from the internet.

```
Private EC2 (10.0.2.5)
      │  wants to reach apt.ubuntu.com
      ▼
NAT Gateway (in public subnet, has Elastic IP)
      │  replaces source IP: 10.0.2.5 → 52.x.x.x
      ▼
Internet Gateway
      │
   Internet
      │  response comes back to 52.x.x.x
      ▼
NAT Gateway  ← translates back to 10.0.2.5
      │
Private EC2 ← gets the response
```

### NAT Gateway vs NAT Instance:

| | NAT Gateway | NAT Instance |
|---|---|---|
| Managed by | AWS (fully managed) | You (EC2) |
| Availability | Highly available per AZ | Single point of failure |
| Bandwidth | Up to 100 Gbps | Limited by instance type |
| Cost | Higher | Cheaper |
| Recommended | ✅ Yes (production) | ❌ Legacy only |

### Important:
- Place NAT Gateway in **public subnet**
- One NAT Gateway per AZ for high availability
- Charges **hourly + per GB** processed — delete when not needed

