## Full Traffic Flow — End to End

```
User types: http://demolb-xxx.eu-north-1.elb.amazonaws.com:8000

1. DNS resolves LB domain → public IP of ALB
2. Request hits Internet Gateway
3. NACL (public subnet inbound) → checked
4. ALB (in public subnet) receives request
5. ALB checks listener rule → forward to demoTG
6. ALB picks healthy target (EC2 in private subnet)
7. NACL (private subnet inbound) → checked
8. EC2 Security Group inbound → checked (allow port 8000 from ALB SG)
9. Python HTTP server handles request → returns HTML
10. Response travels back same path in reverse
11. User sees webpage
```

