```
VPC              → Your isolated network in AWS
CIDR             → IP address range of VPC/subnet
Subnet           → Segment of VPC in one AZ (public/private)
IGW              → Connects VPC to internet (1 per VPC)
Route Table      → Rules for where traffic goes
NAT Gateway      → Private subnet outbound internet access
Load Balancer    → Distributes traffic across instances
Security Group   → Stateful firewall at instance level
NACL             → Stateless firewall at subnet level
DNS              → 10.0.0.2 built-in, Route 53 for custom names
VPC Endpoint     → Private access to AWS services
VPC Peering      → Connect two VPCs privately
Bastion Host     → Jump server for private subnet SSH access
Elastic IP       → Static public IP that persists
ENI              → Virtual network card attached to instance
```

